<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-28-0390 </DOCNO><TEXT>The rising demands for the vehicle's behaviour and its monitoring systemsrequire the use of intelligent evaluation electronics. The informationimportant to the vehicle's user is displayed on the vehicle instrument,which is also ideal for evaluation and representation of all vehiclediagnosis data. The large number of systems in the vehicle demands animproved facility for testing and greater ease of maintenance. One musttry to design these systems to be capable of diagnosis in the future.On board and off board diagnosis are available for the overall diagnosisof the individual systems.</TEXT></DOC>